gn-voice - License
==================

This repository is distributed under a split license.

  * Section A (MIT License) governs the software and the skill-definition
    files - the reusable pipeline.
  * Section B (Reserved Rights) governs the author's own literary works, the
    detailed data derived from them, and the example outputs that reproduce
    the author's style.

Where a single file straddles the boundary (for example a personal genre
pack), the skill-rule and structural text is governed by Section A, and the
author's own writing quoted inside it remains governed by Section B.
Public-domain quotations in wm-prose are not governed by Section B; see
NOTICE Section 3.


